The paper deals with object detection and class recognition in 360° indoor images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for this task, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The dataset creation process involves gathering images and annotating them, which could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
